about.description:
Download a large file from Google Drive.
If you use curl/wget, it fails with a large file because of the security
warning from Google Drive.
about.summary: Download a large file from Google Drive.

name: gdown
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "gdown" %}
{% set version = "3.9.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 83bf8e0049a2e8a0b6d3ae54f70842b58fd37089d05004445b2de184185be0c8

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"
  entry_points:
    - gdown = gdown.cli:main

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    # setuptools is used to determine the version of the package at import time
    - setuptools
    - filelock
    - requests
    - six
    - tqdm

test:
  imports:
    - gdown
  commands:
    - gdown --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/wkentaro/gdown
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Download a large file from Google Drive.'
  description: |
    Download a large file from Google Drive.
    If you use curl/wget, it fails with a large file because of the security
    warning from Google Drive.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - hmaarrfk
